qas.question: How many domain samples are taken during encoding?
Domain samples are transformed into what?
When are 192 samples taken instead of 576?
When 192 samples are taken instead of 576, it is done in an effort to limit what?

context: During encoding, <a0_0>576<a0_0/> time-domain samples are taken and are transformed to 576 <a1_0>frequency-domain samples<a1_0/>.[clarification needed] If <a2_0>there is a transient<a2_0/>, 192 samples are taken instead of 576.
